<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="17">
      <img src="/static/problems/MIT/boriskor/BKimages/two prisms and block sliding.png" alt="Two prisms and a block slide as one object" encrypturl="no"/>
      <br/>
      
        <p>
In the diagram, both prisms and the block have equal masses \(m\). Angle \(\theta\) is given. Both surfaces of the larger prism are frictionless; however, there is friction between the horizontal surface of the smaller prism and the block. The larger prism is being pushed along the floor by a constant unknown force F; as a result, the three objects remain at rest <i>relative to each other. </i>
</p>
      
      <br/>
      <part loncapaid="11">
        <b>Find the acceleration of the system.</b>
        <br/>
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="12" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                    a = 2g tan \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">

                    a = g tan \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                    a = g sin \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                    a = 2g cos \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                    a = g cos \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

                    a = 2g sin \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="13">
        <b>Find the value of the pushing force \(F\).</b>
        <br/>
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="14" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                    F = 6mg tan \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                    F = 6mg sin \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                    F = 6mg cos \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                    F = 3mg cos \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                    F = 3mg sin \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="true">

                    F = 3mg tan \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="15">
        <b>Find the minimum coefficient of static friction \(k\) between the block and the smaller prism that makes it possible for the block to stay at rest relative to the prism.</b>
        <br/>
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="16" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                    k=2tan \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">

                    k=tan \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                    k=2sin \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                    k=sin \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                    k=2cos \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

                    k=cos \(\theta\)
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      
    </parameter>
  </problem>
</html>
